{"id": 231345512, "title": "Love Island stars join in the party on first day of Parklife 2024", "text": "Love Island stars were among the huge crowds enjoying the sun at Parklife this afternoon. Olivia Hawkins, Cally Jane Beach, Kady McDermott, Belle Hassan, Arabella Chi looked glamorous as they posed for pictures at Heaton Park on the first day of the music festival. The former Islanders each donned cowboy boots as they took a break from the music to relax and tuck into some food. Waterloo Road actress Tillie Amartey was also among the tens of thousands of people who have descended on the festival for two epic days of live music, showstopping performances and good vibes. Wearing a slick black two piece, the 21-year-old looked resplendent as the sun beat down on Heaton Park. READ MORE: 30 stylish festival-goers who stole the show on first day of Parklife 2024 Parklife, which is the biggest metropolitan music festival in the UK, will today (June 8) feature sets from Becky Hill, Sugababes, Disclosure, Peggy Gou and Sub Focus . Other acts set to perform today include Four Tet, CamelPhat, Mahala, CASSISDEAD, and Rich Reason. In addition to the live stages, there will be a number of food and drinks stalls dotted across the site, including the festival's first ever alcohol free bar from Kampus-based venue Love From. Before gates opened earlier today, rain threatened those who had come to the huge 600-acre site early doors, but the weather soon switched up for a bit of sunshine as people made their way into the park.", "summary": "A number of famous faces have been spotted among the crowds at Heaton Park", "url": "https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/whats-on/whats-on-news/gallery/love-island-stars-join-party-29318293", "image": "https://i2-prod.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/incoming/article29319065.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_065JPG.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 16:50:32", "author": "Thomas George", "authors": ["Thomas George"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.258}